resolution description: [BLL] Adjunto respuesta de la empresa Initium la cual ya nos dio soporte en otras ocasiones, indicándonos que nos ven la posibilidad del cambio de MAC en la tarjeta de comunicación del TV Manual y confirmando que el fabricante Siemens ya no da soporte a este tipo de equipos por obsolescencia. Por nuestra parte ya lo único que podremos seguir haciendo es la monitorización diaria y tomar la acción de reseteo de la tarjeta del TV Manual cuando la comunicación no sea la adecuada.

incident description: ICC005: MDM batch failed on 8th Apr.
resolution description: ISSUE: ICC005: MDM batch failed on 8th April,2021. ANALYSIS: We have identified that MDM has received large input files from IBP source, hence batch got failed.. BUSINESS IMPACT: Due to this issue there will be delay in customer data update to downsteam system. RESOLTUION: We have splitted the input files and executed the batch with smaller file size, it executed successfully. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No, This is not an issue. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No, This is not an issue.

incident description: ontrol-M Server: Shout by orderno: 0005jlif R35O575 CONTROL-M/Server <Control-M@iberia.es> Wed 07-Ap
resolution description: Issue: Falla el proceso porque no hay datos en el fichero que nos llega de fuera y el proceso falla de forma controlada para revisar que es correcto. Impact: No se genera el fichero de las tasas de Nigeria, pero es correcto. Root Cause: El fichero quincenal que nos llega no tiene información para generar el fichero que saca el proceso. Steps Taken: Se revisa que el fichero recibido es correcto y realmente no tiene información para generar el fichero por lo que borramos el proceso fallado.

incident description: Ha fallado el job D60O10F en zlc , avisar en horario laboral a USCIBMAM 0005jgvr D60O10F
resolution description: Issue: Falla el proceso por sqlcode 8103 contra la BASOFS. Impact: Al no ejecutarse el D60O10F se retrasa la carga de ATPCO, tanto de Inter como de Doméstico. Root Cause: Se produce ese error db2 por no estar recuperada la bbdd en ese momento de ejecución. Steps Taken: Se comprueba que se puede acceder correctamente a la BASOFS a través de query y se relanza el proceso desde el paso fallado renombrando el fichero de salida generado en ese mismo paso. Se comprueba que se ejecuta correctamente.

incident description: [GLE001]SAP CFS - RTR module: SII SAP ERROR MESSAGE & MISSING LOAD IN SII SAP FILE 21 MARCH.
resolution description: Issue: La consola SAP SII rechaza registros de un fichero IBCAR por caracteres extraños. Impact: Retraso en la comunicación de las facturas a SII. Root Cause: Realmente es un error de origen, ya que esos caracteres nos llegan de un fichero externo, pero para no retrasar el envio de las facturas se implementa una traducción automatica de esos caracteres. Steps Taken: Se modifica el programa A42T652 para que traduzca algunos caracteres como tildes o la eñe antes de enviar el fichero a SAP SII.

incident description: [ESC005]: KO degradation of service on the platform
resolution description: Issue: ESC005 - KO degradation of service on the platform. Analysis: We have analyzed the issue and found that reports are not refreshing in GaudiPr4 platform because server is not accessible/ Services was hanged.. There is a degradation of service on the Hyperion platform in gaudipr4. Business Impact: Business were not able to access the reports, This caused delay in staff duties. Resolution: Restarted the GaudiPr4 platform services. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. this is not a recurring issue. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. as the issue is temporary.

Con respecto a las Órdenes de Trabajo AMOS (WO.6414319), pudimos confirmar que las Órdenes SAP 6102587397 ya se generaron el 13/01/2021 y las Cerraron como Ejecutadas el 31/01/2021. Esta información de cierre se envió a AMOS el 31/01/2021 y el WO se cerró con éxito. Pero, este WO, según la información del historial de AMOS, pudimos ver que se reabrieron manualmente el 31/01/2021 y se desasignó del paquete de trabajo anterior el 31/01/2021. Por lo tanto, cierre estos AMOS WO en el extremo de AMOS según las fechas respectivas (31.01.2021) mencionadas anteriormente.

incident description: ALEJANDRIA // SAP: No se puede vincular impresora.
resolution description: Mail sent to user stating that we understand that you are facing issue while printing SAP orders in ZII102/ZII126 transaction. If you are trying to physically print the order in paper, Kindly print via actual printer in ZII102/ZII126 transaction. Otherwise if you are trying digital printing, Kindly use the printer (MZ_DOC_00) for printing SAP orders. Note: For digital printing MZ_DOC_00 is the only printer configured in SAP. Kindly check and let us know if you any help. Since we did not get any response from the user after 3 attempts, we are proceeding to close the incident.

incident description: LINUX_sun - ibcjb5.ib : Filesystem opt-splunkforwarder is occupied 90.00%. Call out to OnCall E-secu
resolution description: Hi Team, Splunk account in the server has been expired hence we couldnt perform the housekeeping in the server. Please execute the below command as root/splunk user to reduce the /opt mount space. Login the server as root/splunk user cd /opt/splunkforwarder/var/log/splunk rm -fr health.log.* metrics.log.* splunkd.log.* [splunk@ibcjb5 ~]$ cd /opt/splunkforwarder/var/log/splunk [splunk@ibcjb5 splunk]$ rm -fr health.log.* metrics.log.* splunkd.log.* [splunk@ibcjb5 splunk]$ df -h . Filesystem Size Used Avail Use% Mounted on /dev/mapper/localVG-lv_splunkforwarder 504M 137M 342M 29% /opt/splunkforwarder

incident description: Fallo Software: DKIM / DMARC INcident with no reply mailbox @gmail.com
resolution description: issue: emails from Salesforce were not sent from noreply@iberia.com to gmail. impact: it was huge as no customer with gmail address were able to receive the email. Analysis: It was due to DMARC policy changes as Iberia end. Not sure how it suddenlty impacted but it needed a DKIM key generation at Salesforce and then it was included to add the DNS entries at Iberia Network side. Resolution: created a DKIM key, and Host: sfdc-pro-iberiacom._domainkey.iberia.com Type: TXT Value: v=DKIM1; k=rsa; p=MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEAqhZM2il7DVlDCu3iR and activated it Problem ticket: NO, issue was fixed after doing changes. Preventive measures: No, the issue was fixed.

incident description: [CARGO PORTAL]LHR - ECSD - Unable to generate Regulate entity Category number for AWB's
resolution description: <Issue>::Add RA button was not working for the user while editing an in eCSD in portal <Impact>:: User not able to work. <Analysis>:: There was a bug in the code where if GB RA was fetched from user preference, then that was being checked against the EU RA table AGENTES_ACREDITADOS and since this value did not existed in that table the code did not do anything from this point onwards. <Steps Taken to Resolve>:: Added an else statement to populate the RA code fetched from user preference in fields box 1 or box 14 if that RA code is GB and even if that did not existed in the EU RA table. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).>:: NO. <Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No)> :: NA

incident description: IB.COM INFORM-GESTION:PROCESO reservas informes de gestión de ib.com fallido por rotación PROCAPL2
resolution description: Issue: The shell script trata_pnr_resu.sh on host sercoml-scort is failing (the script is in the path  /procusers/percom/bin). Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that the problem is related to ssh conection between the hosts  sercoml-scort.ib and procaplc.ib. Business Impact: User will not be able to see any data as data will not be loaded due to job failure. Resolution: Below steps has been performed to fix this issue: 1. Request has been raised to Linux team to check. 2. As per the Linux team “node 2 (the cluster is in this node right now) is configured user bvlog as deny connections”. 3. Linux team allowed the connection. 4. Script has been working fine now. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. this is not a recurring issue. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. as the issue is temporary.

incident description: LINUX_ibm - El job: R15O225 con OrderID: 5jnmi del DataCenter: CTM_SERVER en la maquina: zlc, Aplica
resolution description: ISsue: Fallo R15O225 Impact. MEdio Root causes: Falla por descuadre. El motivo del descuadre es que estos billetes están en moneda VES, pero al ser una moneda tan débil, el sistema no soporta el importe real del billete, que según hemos calculado para la tarifa sería 1.733.774.388,45. Al soportar 11 dígitos, se queda en 73377438845, que es justo el importe que se puede ver en el contable. Este problema no sólo afecta al contable, sino también al ingreso y demás tablas en NBDP. Por otro lado, estos casos son RTK, desconocemos si este mes problema se puede estar dando en emisiones normales, ya que el propio fichero BSP sólo soporta 11 dígitos. Podría estar dándose y que no esté siendo detectado, pues el contable no descuadraría por no tener una referencia de un billete previo con el cuadrar la información. Steps taken: Se informa a cliente después de conformidad del mismo a continuar el contable.

resolution description: Issue: Could you please raise a ‘P3’ incident and assign it to “Aplicaciones BI” queue. Incident Description: Error in consolidated Operational CRQ Report. The data is mismatching between total entries and data provided in the record below. Analysis: We have analyzed the issue and found that Column “Fecha Imputación” only contains date not timestamp so if there are 4 entries for single day with entry 1 for 2 hour ,entry 2 for 2 hour, entry 3 for 2 hour and entry 4 for 1 hour then OBI is considering entry 1, entry 2 and entry 3 as a duplicate entries and it is showing only 2 entries for entry 1 and entry 4. Business Impact: Team will not able to view the correct report. Resolution: We have added one more column in the report with “number of entries” for daily basis. It will show consolidated total hours for daily basis with number of entries for that day. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. this is not a recurring issue. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. as the issue is temporary.

incident description: CIP: On Business OB23929052 – Bookings JKR2D + JKSTN not linked to account /L
resolution description: Issue : Customer has reported that the bookings JKR2D + JKSTN are not linked to the account OB23929052. Impact : Users were not able to check if the bookings were not linked with account and this will cause financial loss & this will cause bad customer experience. Analysis: We checked with comarch and they have checked at their end and they have informed us that the booking was an accrual booking and gets linked to account from 3-4 days of travel date. Resolution : We checked with comarch and they have checked at their end and they have informed us that the booking was an accrual booking and gets linked to account from 3-4 days of travel date. We checked and bookings were updated on onbusiness portal. We asked customer to check and confirm if they are able to see the bookings. Customer confirmed that we can close this incident. Problem ticket: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

incident description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online NO AVISAR ON-CALL Necesidad
resolution description: Issue Description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online Business Impact: no impact in this case, however online emisions could be impacted Analysis: We have checked and and observed that there were successful transactions for 10/04/21 after 14:00.Also, we are getting this alert very frequently since few days now. As per our analysis, since March 3rd 21 the traffic on Amadeus is very low. It seems that certain traffic has been moved to NetPlus from Amadeus because from the same moment of time there is an upgradation in NetPlus Payments. And, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform(please find the attachment) This alert triggers from Splunk for the emissions happens via Amadeus, so because of degradation in traffic on Amadeus, the EOL transactions are also decreasing. Action taken: no action has been taken here as we can see successful transactions on 10 April Problem Ticket: not required, no more alerts occurred since then Preventive Measures: alerts have already set up for this

ISSUE: ICC005: Wrong email updated in Salesforce for customer 'IB19949403',even though correct email was updated in ATOS. ANALYSIS: It was observed the this customer has different email id registered for customer\tutor account. Last update for this customer was reveived for tutor account with tutor email id. This tutor email id replaced the customer email id and Tutor email id updated in Salesforce. Hence there is discrepancy in email. BUSINESS IMPACT: Due to this issue, customer email is flipping from customer to tutor to customer email Id in downstream system and customer is not able to see his/her correct email in Salesforce. This is creating a data discrepancy between upstream and downstream system. RESOLTUION: We have reprocessed the record with new email and same has been updated to downstream system. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: Yes(PBI000000085358), this is known issue and We are already working on the permanen fix. CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: Yes, once fix will be deployed against the PR which we have raised for this issue.

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_*_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO GENERIC_ACCRUAL Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

[ICC001] SALESFORCE MARKETING CLOUD Santander customers - relations table
resolution description: issue: Dumbo Onboarding customers not present in Mkt relation table at CI end. impact: email information not sent from onboarding journey. Analysis:all new customers coming from Santander before the 21st January 2021 are not in the Iberia_pro.mkt_relations_processed table in Datalake. The mkt_relations table relates the salesforce id to the iberia plus card id and a feed is sent from salesforce into this table daily uploading with the new customers. So just to also clarify the customers missing from the table are onboarded with Santander and never been in the Iberia plus programme before. So we can see they have been sent an email in Saleforce through the onboarding journey but because they are not in the above table we cannot relate them to a iberia plus card id. There was a change made on the 21st of January that helped this issue but we are still missing those customers onboarded before that date. I have suggested we manually find these customers in the salesforce, export and upload them manually into the table but unsure if we can find those customers Resolution: provided the data after founding the information related. will provide data via REQ. Problem ticket: NO, not an issue as now data needs to be provided. Preventive measures: No, the issue was fixed.

Issue: Consulta sobre valoración RTK Impact: Bajo Root Causes: Ya se ha revisado este tema, explicamos detalladamente el importe a cero en este RTK. El billete 2393765640 se valora a partir del tomado 2393579652 que ya tiene valor 0. Que este otro billete tenga importe a cero se debe a dos situaciones juntas que se dan en el momento en el que se valora a partir del tomado 3788360931: • La venta del billete tomado aún no está en NBDP, si la venta hubiera estado cargada hubiera recuperado el valor de la misma y no hubiera ido a cero. Esto se debe al propio funcionamiento del sistema, ya que el billete 3788360931 llegó por agencias (Republica Dominicana) el día 10 de enero, pero esa semana no entró a control de cuadre hasta el día 22. En cambio, el nuevo billete 2393579652 llegó cómo delegación el día 14, y el día 16 ya entró al control de cuadre. • La situación anterior confluyó con que en la NBDP sí estaba una utilización de vuelo del billete tomado, si no hubiera estado, el sistema habría recuperado el importe de CRS. Ahora mismo hay una utilización duplicada en el vuelo del cupón 01 del billete 3788360931 (IB6500-SDQ-MAD), ya nos decís si queréis que le pasemos la incidencia al sistema origen del vuelo para ver si ese cupón efectivamente se ha volado. Steps taken: Se informa al cliente.
departamento cliente: RESP. CTROL ING Y GEST. A (3KEMI0)

4.29-[OPTIMA]-User update : The user cannot create any restrictions. It only requests an availability for certain criteria: - Routing - Date - Commodity - Pieces - Weight - Dimensions - Allocation - etc. Based on the availability response received from Optima, the booking request is made. Therefore, if there is any restriction in Optima for the dimensions of the request, it should not offer availability to the user or at least inform of such restriction. 4.28-[OPTIMA]-Final Chaser has been sent to the user 4.26-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.20-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.19-[OPTIMA]-AFLS updated the following : We have checked the user reported issue and understand that when performing the availability search for MIL - ORD and the length given in the request is 330. And when performing the booking for MXP - ORD the length given in the request is 362.But the user expectation is to reject the booking due to no large booking options for ORD. In OPTIMA we can restrict the bookings based on the length ,width ,height ,MAX_NBR_PIECES ,MAX_WT_PER_PIECE , MAX_SUM_W_L_H by using the PIECE_LMT_BY_PROD restriction. When we were checking for the restriction for the ORD by matching the above attributes we couldn't see PIECE_LMT_BY_PROD restriction created for ORD. Can you please ask the user to create a PIECE_LMT_BY_PROD restriction for ORD to restrict the large bookings ? 4.16-[OPTIMA]-The local office informed the customer that there were no large booking options for ORD, however, those options were shown to the user as available, so the customer asks us if the availability is wrong. Currently pending with AFLS 4.15-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.13-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.9-[OPTIMA]-Chaser has been sent to the user 4.7-[OPTIMA]-Below update from AFLS has been shard with the user : ____________________________________ From the above ticket, we understand that this booking made with the dimensions L x W x H 362x90x299 and booking has been accepted, but the expectation is to reject due to the size of the cargo. Please let us know if our understanding is correct or please explain in detail the issue which you are facing. Could you please check and advise us accordingly ? 4.6-INC20589740 raised at AFLS's end

(BT) Parece ser que debido a algún corte de tensión se averiaron las fuentes de corriente de 3 switches del H5, lo que provocaba que por derivación se cayera la corriente en todo el rack. Tras revisión conjunta con Covi, tenemos: uno de ellos es el cabecera (CE_HAG5-1_172.25.2.3), que funciona gracias a la fuente redundante, pues la principal provoca derivaciones y se deja apagada; los otros dos (CE_HAG5-1S4_172.25.3.185 y CE_HAG5-1S6_172.25.3.187) se sustituyen. Se comprueba con Covi que tras esta sustitución queda el rack funcionando correctamente. Se abrirá cambio para sustitución del switch cabecera.

He revisado este caso, el problema es que para el host el asiento no está pagado. En la traza de la operación no veo ni el cambio de asiento ni el pago del mismo, esto es, entiendo que, porque lo hacéis por fuera, directamente en Resiber, esto no puede ser así ya que para cki este asiento no está pagado. Las llamadas correctas serian, después del ACCEPT PX, debéis llamar al SEAT MAP (se muestra el mapa de asientos), CHANGE PX (cambio de asiento), INFO ANCILLARIES (información de pagos pendientes), PAY ANCILLARIES (pago de ancillaries, ya sean asientos o maletas) y por ultimo, BOARDING CARD ( tarjeta de embarque)

Issue - SAP did not generate order for AMOS work order (WO.6723816) Impacts - Might affect planned maintenance activities. Analysis - With respect to AMOS Work Orders (WO.6723816), we were able to confirm that SAP Orders 4100096478 were already generated on 06/04/2020 and closed them as Executed on 06/09/2020. When the closing information was sent to AMOS on 06/09/2020, WO were assigned a different work package. This is why the WO is in the Open state. Therefore, close these WO AMOS at the AMOS end according to the respective dates (06/09/2020). Later user was not able to re-open the closed SAP order (4100096478). We have provided the missing authorization for user ID. User confirmed that issue is resolved. Problem ticket Required - NO Can this incident be prevented - No, as long as business removes the WO from WP after SAP order generation, this issue continues to occur.

incident description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online NO AVISAR ON-CALL Necesidad
resolution description: Issue Description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online Business Impact: no impact in this case, however online emisions could be impacted Analysis: We are getting this alert very frequently since few days now. As per our analysis, since March 3rd 21 the traffic on Amadeus is very low. It seems that certain traffic has been moved to NetPlus from Amadeus because from the same moment of time there is an upgradation in NetPlus Payments. And, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform(please find the attachment) This alert triggers from Splunk for the emissions happens via Amadeus, so because of degradation in traffic on Amadeus, the EOL transactions are also decreasing. Action taken: no action has been taken here as not required. platform is fine Problem Ticket: not required, no more alerts occurred since then Preventive Measures: alerts have already set up for this

Issue: KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FICHERO OFFLINE_ENROLMENT (Comarch --> Iberia Cards) KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO PARTIAL_REVERSAL_*_08_27_28_IBC.trn KO in OBHCIP OBHCIP: KO proceso FISION FICHERO IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT Analysis: Analyzed the issue and found that we have not received the files in the below location that's why load plan got failed. files directory: /obhcip/input/comarch Business Impact: Delay in file execution will impact Iberia cards since it holds Reversal points data, consumed by partners of the loyalty program and hence the users will not be able to see the updated Reversal points against their Iberia Cards. Resolution: Re ran the ODI Load plan for Partial Reversal file to successfully process the file. PKG_OFFLINE_ENROLMENT_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_PARTIAL_REVERSAL_trn_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_GENERIC_ACCRUAL_trn_out PKG_FISION_FICHEROS_IB_CARD_ASSIGMENT_trn_out CAN THIS ISSUE BE PREVENTED?: No. The File was delayed from the source Team and therefore, no issue with the application. PROBLEM TICKET REQUIRED?: No. As the files are received from the source Team. There was delay in sending the files due to which the load Plan failed.

incident description: [COM037]: No hemos recibido el fichero de IBPLUS_Monthly - IBP_OPERATIONSM_20210301_000000
resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has reported that they have not received IBPLUS Monthly file for February. impact : If AIP will not receive this data ,they will not be able to generate the reports at their end required for business. Analysis : We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibplliveon exchange node and file was not available and we also checked the s3 bucket to make sure if the files were archived. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.We have checked the path on exchange node where these files are sent by source at user ftpicc003ibpllive on exchange node and the files was not available. We followed-up with ATOS team for the reason for missing file. 2. ATOS confirmed that they have transferred the file correctly. 3.We again checked at the destination location for the IBPLUS files. And the files IBP_OPERATIONSM_20210201_000000 was present at the location /ibftplinint/live/ftpicc003loyalive/ . 4. we contacted AIP team to check and verify if the files are available. AIP confirmed that the files are received . Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

incident description: Incidencia Resiber - Ausencia de información en Resiber TKT
resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has reported that the ticket 0752392542107 updated information was not received. impact : If AIP will not receive this data ,they will not be able to generate the reports at their end required for business. Analysis : We have investigated at our end and noticed that the information was not received, so we contacted source team to provide us reason for the missing information. Steps Taken to Resolve: 1.We have investigated at our end and noticed that the information was not received, so we contacted source team to provide us reason for the missing information. 2.We contacted source TKT team and they have informed us that the file currently sent from TKT contains data about tickets issued the previous day. They are not sending information about revalidations or updated information on those tickets. Ticket 0752392542107 was issued on September 18th and reported on September 19th. So operations on February 22th on ticket 0752392542107 are not reported on feb 22 file nor any other file. 3. we informed AIP and AIP confirmed that the information is sufficient and we can close this incident. . Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data.

resolution description: Issue:AIP has reported that they have not received google analytics file . Analysis:We have checked that Google Analytics files were not generated as google query tables were updated late after the crontab run the process responsible to generate files. Impact:If Google analytics files are not generated ,AIP will not receive the files which will further lead to delay in generation of reports at AIP end. Resolution:We have checked the files were generated in next run successfully and placed on exchange node for AIP to consume the files. Problem Ticket:NO-Google Query tbles were upadte late due to which files were not generated on time . Preventive Action:YES We have taken care by including Daily Daily Health Check to prevent such incidents.

Issue - Gap in SAP FR Orders Impacts : Planned Aircraft maintenance activities is affected Analysis - Checked whether the Revision data contains any other Gaps. Steps Taken to Resolve the issue - Requested user to create 1 Dummy Order. Once user created it, We made the necessary data correction. User confirmed that the issue is resolved. Problem ticket Required - No, We have a Work Order in Place to do the necessary code fix as part of the permanent solution. Can this incident be prevented - No USV DGMI : As discussed in TEAMS, the problem with the FR gap was successfully resolved on the IP1 system after the necessary data correction. As confirmed by you through TEAMS, we proceed to close this Incident. We are progressing remediation testing on the IQ1 system to handle similar issues in the future.

resolution description: 4.21-[OPTIMA]-After the IP address change, the system is able to connect and as the queue are build up it may take some time to clean the pending message queue. ISSUE: AIP has reported that they have received information for same customer but with two associated id_golden_record in MDM customer file. IMPACT: Data files are required by AIP.AIP will not be able to generate the reports for analysis and these reports are used by business. Analysis: We asked MDM team to check at their end why the records where not correctly merged at MDM end. Steps Taken to Resolve: We asked MDM team to check at their end why the records where not correctly merged at MDM end. MDM team investigated the issue at their end and informed us that the records are merged at MDM end correctly and populates in MERGES_20210422_111242.txt file. AIP confirmed that the records are merged correctly. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data

Problem ticket Required - No Can this incident be prevented - Yes, if the aircrafts belongs to IBS, the necessary data has to be maintained for the aircraft via ZID341MPD_01.

(Engine - 697133) Impacts - Might affect engine maintenance activities Analysis - Based on our conversation at TEAMS, we have manually removed these 12118618 and 12118619 devices from the ZIV. The senders are blocked and the emails removed. The phishing site is requested to be block on the Iberia proxy in case INC000001519165.

[SAP BASIS] Buenos días, El problema del hisotiral de SAP borrado en su equipo es un problema de su PC. Desde SAP no podemos hacer nada. Como mucho podemos adjuntar el siguiente enlace en el que explica los diferentes motivos por el que se ha borrado dicho historial en su equipo. https://www.blogdesap.com/2014/06/funcionamiento-historial-entradas-sap.html Seguramente, cuando usaron su equipo para instalar Office, se borró alguna configuración de SAP. Seguramente lo único que se pueda hacer es empezar a trabajarr y poco a poco volver a crear un nuevo historial. En el caso de que el historial no se genere es necesario que abra una petición para volver volver a reinstalar SAP GUI en su equipo de nuevo. Un saludo, Juan Palacios SAP Basis Consultant

Issue - Incident was related to Informe de grupos Infoges. User was not able to extract the data of Reserved Groups from Infoges. Impact - User was extracting the report with empty data. So, revenue was getting empacted. analysis - We analyzed that the user created in INFOGES was not correct with some column values. So, we updated the row in INFOGES table with correct values. resolution - We updated the user values in INFOGES table. "GERENCIA" column was with values '0' that's why user was not able to extract the data. Now we updated the column value with '00'. User successfully extracted the report from INFOGES hence, we are closing the incident. can this issue be prevented: no, this was temporary issue. Problem Ticket Required (Y/N) : No, as the issue is already resolved

incident description: FALLO CONTROL ERRORES INFOGES & Air Nostrum - (PROCAPLC/BDGL)
resolution description: Issue - ERRORES in control_error table of INFOGES and YIELD MANAGEMENT. There was failure of carga_rehorcam process in both the applications. Impact - revenue was getting impacted as it is needed for the analysis for good performance of daily operations. analysis - we checked the control_error table there was error "Falta carga: Rehorcam_V_I2" & "Falta carga: Rehorcam_Dif". We generally receive file at 8:00 p.m but today the file was received late at 8:00 a.m. So there was failure in process. resolution - We renamed the file in INFOGES and then launched the carga_rehorcam process in INFOGES and then in YW we followed the same procedure. Process was successfully launched. Hence, we are closing the INCIDENT. can this issue be prevented: no, this was temporary issue. Problem Ticket Required (Y/N) : No, as the issue is already resolved

incident description: Ordenador que trabaja con hyperion sin conexion a internet
resolution description: [SSI]: Buenos días, el equipo de soporte indica lo siguiente: "Ya se ha revisado por BT y Aena y la red está bien. Debe ponerse en contacto el usuario con su soporte local ya que es un equipo externo y EUC no puede hacer nada. Adjunto respuesta de Aena de la anterior incidencia: No se han encontrado problemas a nivel de RMS, la MAC del equipo es visible desde la electrónica de red, pero el equipo no presenta tráfico al switch del aeropuerto y, por tanto, no coge IP. El equipo debe ser revisado por el personal informático que lleve el mismo. Quedamos a la espera de su respuesta. No responda a este mensaje ya que se trata de una respuesta automática del sistema. Contacte nuevamente con nosotros por teléfono al 915874700 o por email al ssi@iberia.es aportando el nº de referencia de su incidencia. Muchas gracias, Un cordial saludo.

incident description: No hemos recibido los ficheros de MDM correspondientes al día 21 de Abril
resolution description: ISSUE: AIP has not received MDM files for 21st March. IMPACT: These files are required by AIP.AIP will not be able to generate the reports for analysis and these reports are used by business. Analysis: We have checked ftpicc005mdm_live and ftpicc003mdm_live user on exchange node (172.21.232.199/ibftplinint.ib), the files were not available. We checked with MDM team and they informed us that the files were generated late, as the MDM batch took more time. Steps Taken to Resolve: We have checked ftpicc005mdm_live and ftpicc003mdm_live user on exchange node (172.21.232.199/ibftplinint.ib). Files were not available on exchange node, We checked with MDM team and they informed us that the files were generated late, as the MDM batch took more time. After the file generation we informed AIP and AIP confirmed that the files were received successfully. Problem Ticket Required? (Yes, No).: No , as the issue is related to source and target data. Can this incident be prevented? (Yes, No): No , as the issue is related to source and target data

incident description: MERCURY: Abrir incidencia por falta de información en ficheros Infoges - 20210428
resolution description: Issue - Incident was related to extraction process of the files that arrive at Mercury from INFOGES is reviewed because it has been detected that in the file infoges_bevde_275_20210428.txt the capacity for May, June and July of the MAD PMI 3918 flight has not arrived. Impact - User did not received the data for May, June, July of flight 3918. So, revenue was getting empacted. analysis - After analyzing the code we found that data related to flight “3918” in INFOGES for DIA= 5, which is not for date 27th Apr 2021. resolution - We have checked the process "CARGA_DATOS_RESERVAS_I2" and "CARGA_DATOS_RESERVAS_I2_SH". We have many conditions during generation of this file some of them are mentioned below. WHERE V.NUMVUELO = VU.NUMVUELO AND V.ORIGEN = VU.ORIGEN AND V.DESTINO = VU.DESTINO AND V.DIA = 5 AND V.FECHA_VUELO <= TRUNC(SYSDATE-2) + 275 AND ((V.TIPO_AVION LIKE ('%/I2%') OR TO_NUMBER(V.NUMVUELO) BETWEEN 3500 AND 3999) OR V.NUMVUELO IN (Select DISTINCT NUMVUELO from PARAM_I2. Received user confirmation. Hence, closing the ticket. Can this issue be prevented: no, this was temporary issue. Problem Ticket Required (Y/N) : No, as the issue is already resolved

incident description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online NO AVISAR ON-CALL Necesidad
resolution description: Issue Description: ALERTA-CRI:Iberia.com portal Splunk Alert: Alerta errores emision online Business Impact: no impact in this case, however online emisions could be impacted Analysis: We are getting this alert very frequently since few days now. As per our analysis, since March 3rd 21 the traffic on Amadeus is very low. It seems that certain traffic has been moved to NetPlus from Amadeus because from the same moment of time there is an upgradation in NetPlus Payments. And, there is no overall degradation in payments on platform(please find the attachment) This alert triggers from Splunk for the emissions happens via Amadeus, so because of degradation in traffic on Amadeus, the EOL transactions are also decreasing. Action taken: no action has been taken here. we will review the alert as per the current situation and if required we will take necessary actions Problem Ticket: not required, no more alerts occurred since then Preventive Measures: alerts have already set up for this
